Package: squish
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: @MAINTAINER@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/squish-compression/squish
Depends: libc6
Description: context-mixing file compressor (command-line tool)
 The squish command-line tool compresses and decompresses files and whole
 directory trees, outcompressing zip -9, bzip2 -9, and rar -m5 across a standard
 corpus at a higher CPU cost. It lists archives and extracts single members
 without inflating the rest.
 .
 The tool is statically linked; the libsquish shared library is packaged
 separately as libsquish1 (runtime) and libsquish-dev (development files).
